OL,3,CChicken producer denies claims their
OL,4,Cfarm manure is polluting the River Wye
OL,6,F"This destruction of one the UK's most
OL,7,Fbeautiful natural areas cannot
OL,8,Fcontinue, which is why we are bringing
OL,9,Fthis legal action."JThe claim is
OL,10,Fsupported by charity River Action.
OL,11,FChair and founder Charles Watson said:
OL,12,F"With around a quarter of the
OL,13,Fcountry's chickens now being reared in
OL,14,Fthe catchment of the River Wye, the
OL,15,Fwaste emitting from this totally
OL,16,Funsustainable concentration of poultry
OL,17,Fproduction has blighted communities
OL,18,Facross the region.J"With a huge
OL,19,Fpercentage of this industry controlled
OL,20,Fby Avara, it is entirely appropriate
OL,21,Fthat the polluter must now be made to
OL,22,Fpay to clean up the mess we believe it
OL,23,Fhas created and subsequently profited
OL,24,Ffrom.
